===Etymology===
:from the Latin ''id est'', meaning ''that is''

===[[adverb]]===
#that is, in other words, that is to say
#:I.e. is used to explain or clarify a statement by either (exhaustively) listing  options or by rephrasing the previous statement. I.e. is always followed by a [[comma]] when used in it's function as a clarifier. When used in a sentence, i.e. should be used parenthetically (i.e., embraced in parentheses).